NO

2

/NO

X

 ratio monitored downwind, no long-term complex 
photochemical calculation is needed. Thus, it makes the modeling 
exercise much simpler, yet still provides results consistent with 
available plume observational studies. 

The method is conservative since, in many cases, maximum 
estimated ground level NO

X

 concentration may occur prior to 
thorough mixing of the plume. A second, less important, source of 
conservatism is that the existing NO

